.TH "unshieldv3" "1" "2026-06-05" "unshieldv3 User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
\f[B]unshieldv3\f[R] - extract InstallShield V3 (Z) archives
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]unshieldv3\f[R] \f[I]COMMAND\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]]
[\f[I]arguments\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]unshieldv3\f[R] extracts files from InstallShield V3 archives (Z
format).
.PP
InstallShield Z format is a compressed archive format used by version 3
of the InstallShield installation software.
Z files can be recognised by their magic marker:
\f[V]13 5D 65 8C 3A 01 02 00\f[R].
Contained files are compressed with the PKware implode algorithm.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]help\f[R]
Display a usage summary and exit.
.TP
\f[B]info\f[R] \f[I]ARCHIVE.Z\f[R]
Show metadata for \f[I]ARCHIVE.Z\f[R]: file count, compressed size,
uncompressed size, and multi-volume information when applicable.
.TP
\f[B]list\f[R] [\f[B]-v\f[R]] \f[I]ARCHIVE.Z\f[R]
List the contents of \f[I]ARCHIVE.Z\f[R].
With \f[B]-v\f[R], also display the uncompressed size and the timestamp
of each file.
.TP
\f[B]extract\f[R] \f[I]ARCHIVE.Z\f[R] \f[I]DESTDIR\f[R]
Extract all files from \f[I]ARCHIVE.Z\f[R] into the existing directory
\f[I]DESTDIR\f[R], recreating the internal directory structure.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
List files in an archive with verbose output:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
unshieldv3 list -v NETSCAPE.Z
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Show archive metadata:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
unshieldv3 info NETSCAPE.Z
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Extract an archive to /tmp/out:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
unshieldv3 extract NETSCAPE.Z /tmp/out
\f[R]
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
An error occurred (archive not found, destination directory missing,
write failure, or invalid usage).
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
Please report issues at <https://github.com/wfrisch/unshieldv3/issues>.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]unshield\f[R](1) \[em] extracts later InstallShield archive
formats.
